fields.short_bio: Saer de Quincy, 1st Earl of Winchester (c. 1170 â€“ 3 November 1219) was one of the leaders of the baronial rebellion against John, King of England, and a major figure in both the kingdoms of Scotland and England in the decades around the turn of the twelfth and thirteenth centuries.

fields.title: Earl
fields.short_bio: Robert Crawley, 7th Earl of Grantham (b. 1866) is the Earl of Grantham in the TV series Downton Abbey. He is portrayed by actor Hugh Bonneville.

fields.title: Earl
fields.short_bio: Lord Emsworth is a recurring fictional character in the Blandings stories by British comic writer P. G. Wodehouse. He is the amiable and somewhat absent-minded head of the large Threepwood family.

fields.title: Earl
fields.short_bio: William, Earl of Glenallan, otherwise Lord Glenallan, is a character in Sir Walter Scott's 1816 novel The Antiquary, a Scottish aristocrat whose life has been ruined by the suicide of his wife and the belief that he has unwittingly committed incest
